3. Print all possible Knight's tours on a chessboard

Description

Given a chess board, print all paths a knight can take to visit each square.

Example

 1  50  45  62  31  18   9  64
46  61  32  49  10  63  30  17
51   2  47  44  33  28  19   8
60  35  42  27  48  11  16  29
41  52   3  34  43  24   7  20
36  59  38  55  26  21  12  15
53  40  57   4  23  14  25   6
58  37  54  39  56   5  22  13

Note that a knight's tour is not always possible.

\(n\) Number of possible tours
\(1\) \(1\)
\(2\) \(0\)
\(3\) \(0\)
\(4\) \(0\)
\(5\) \(1,728\)
\(\dots\) \(\dots\)

fun knightsTour(boardSize: Int) {
  val board = Array(boardSize) { IntArray(boardSize) }
  // Complete //
}

data class Square(val row: Int, val col: Int)

fun Array<IntArray>.print() {
  for (r in 0..<size) {
    for (c in 0..<size) {
      print("%2d ".format(this[r][c]))
    }
    println()
  }
}

fun Array<IntArray>.validKnightMove(row: Int, col: Int): Stream<Square> {
  return Stream.of(
    Square(row - 2, col - 1),
    Square(row - 2, col + 1),
    Square(row - 1, col - 2),
    Square(row - 1, col + 2),
    Square(row + 1, col - 2),
    Square(row + 1, col + 2),
    Square(row + 2, col - 1),
    Square(row + 2, col + 1),
  ).filter { it.row in 0..<size }
    .filter { it.col in 0..<size }
    .filter { this[it.row][it.col] == 0 }
}

fun knightsTour(boardSize: Int) {
  val board = Array(boardSize) { IntArray(boardSize) }
  helper(board, Square(row = 0, col = 0), moveNumber = 1)
}

fun helper(board: Array<IntArray>, square: Square, moveNumber: Int) {
  board[square.row][square.col] = moveNumber
  if (moveNumber == board.size * board.size) {
    board.print()
    println("--------------")
    board[square.row][square.col] = 0
    return
  }

  for (next in board.validKnightMove(square.row, square.col)) {
    helper(board, next, moveNumber + 1)
  }
  board[square.row][square.col] = 0
}
